title: Northrop Grumman wins $45 million Space Force contract to launch small weather satellite
summary: Northrop Grumman won a $45.5 million contract to launch a small weather satellite in 2025, the U.S. Space Force announced May 25.

title: BREAKING! ULA To Roll Back Vulcan Rocket, Flight Readiness Firing Delayed
summary: ULA has announced a last-minute delay in the engine flight readiness testing for its highly anticipated Vulcan rocket. The test fire, originally scheduled for today, was halted approximately three hours before the planned ignition.

title: NASA to Discuss Science on Next SpaceX Cargo Launch to Space Station
summary: NASA will host a media teleconference at 2 p.m. EDT Tuesday, May 30, to discuss the next science investigations, technology demonstrations, crew supplies, and hardware bound for the International Space Station aboard SpaceX’s 28th commercial resupply services mission for the agency.

title: Virgin Galactic makes first suborbital spaceflight in nearly two years
summary: Virgin Galactic’s SpaceShipTwo suborbital vehicle flew to space for the first time in nearly two years May 25 on what the company projected to be the vehicle’s final test flight before commencing commercial operations.

title: Investing in Space: Who wins in the Elon Musk versus Jeff Bezos moon race
summary: The billionaire race to the moon is on, but it doesn’t matter whether Elon Musk or Jeff Bezos gets there first – either way, NASA wins.

title: Viasat’s Inmarsat acquisition clears all regulatory hurdles
summary: Viasat has secured all regulatory clearances needed to buy British satellite operator Inmarsat after getting unconditional approval from the European Commission May 25.

title: South Korea’s KSLV-2 rocket launches seven satellites, one unaccounted for
summary: South Korea’s KSLV-2 rocket put seven satellites, including one equipped with synthetic aperture radar, into sun-synchronous orbit May 25, although an eighth cubesat is believed to have not deployed properly.

title: VSS Unity conducts first powered flight since Branson’s trip in 2021
summary: After a nearly two-year pause in flights, starting after a deviation from controlled airspace during Sir Richard Branson’s flight in July 2021, the Virgin Galactic SpaceShipTwo VSS Unity made its first powered flight since the eventful Unity 22 mission.

title: Virgin Galactic completes Unity 25 spaceflight in key final test before commercial service
summary: Virgin Galactic launched its first spaceflight in nearly two years on Thursday, a key final test for the space tourism company before it begins flying commercial passengers.

title: At long last, the glorious future we were promised in space is on the way
summary: "It is gratifying to see folks coming around."
